---
interface Props {
  base: string;
}
const { base } = Astro.props;
---

<div
  class="theatre-modal"
  id="about-modal"
  data-theatre-modal
  data-theatre-theme="about"
  hidden
>
  <div class="theatre-modal__backdrop" data-theatre-modal-close></div>
  <div class="theatre-modal__frame">
    <button
      class="theatre-modal__close"
      type="button"
      aria-label="Close about modal"
      data-theatre-modal-close
    >
      <picture class="theatre-modal__close-picture" aria-hidden="true">
        <source
          media="(max-width: 540px)"
          srcset={`${base}/img/close-mobile.svg`}
        />
        <img
          class="theatre-modal__close-icon"
          src={`${base}/img/close.svg`}
          alt=""
        />
      </picture>
    </button>
    <div
      class="theatre-modal__panel"
      role="dialog"
      aria-modal="true"
      aria-labelledby="about-modal-title"
      tabindex="-1"
    >
      <div class="theatre-modal__content">
        <div class="theatre-modal__media">
          <img
            class="theatre-modal__media-image"
            src={`${base}/img/whatever_it_takes.png`}
            alt=""
            aria-hidden="true"
          />
        </div>
        <header class="theatre-modal__header">
          <h2 class="theatre-modal__title" id="about-modal-title">
            Thanks for stopping by!
          </h2>
        </header>

        <section class="theatre-modal__section">
          <div class="theatre-modal__prose">
            <p class="theatre-modal__text">
              I've been designing and building software professionally for 15+
              years. Whether it's evolving what already exists or creating
              something entirely new, I love figuring out what to build.
            </p>
            <p class="theatre-modal__text">
              Originally from Hungary, I'm a dad of three, happily married, and
              living in southern Sweden.
            </p>
            <p class="theatre-modal__text">
              In my free time, I play Nintendo games, enjoy retro platformers,
              and do sports. I'm also passionate about pixel art.
            </p>
            <p class="theatre-modal__text">
              My first name, Jozsef, is the Hungarian version of Joseph. In
              Hungarian, it's often shortened to Jozsi. When pronounced in
              English, it often sounds like Yoshi. The nickname stuck, and
              that's what most people call me.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="theatre-modal__section">
          <h3 class="theatre-modal__eyebrow">Design? How do I do it?</h3>
          <div class="theatre-modal__prose">
            <p class="theatre-modal__text">Not screens. Flows.</p>
            <p class="theatre-modal__text">
              Start with a design concept for where we're headed, ideally a
              video showing the expected user journey. Then break it down into
              buildable chunks. Production is always the reference.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="theatre-modal__section">
          <h3 class="theatre-modal__eyebrow">A quote I return to often</h3>
          <blockquote class="theatre-modal__quote">
            <p class="theatre-modal__text">
              "Most of the things I am most proud of have come from just doing
              the thing
            </p>
            <p class="theatre-modal__text">
              Most people would rather ask questions, debate, etc
            </p>
            <p class="theatre-modal__text">
              Most decisions are two way doors and you are often times rewarded
              for taking the initiative"
            </p>
            <footer class="theatre-modal__quote-attribution">
              — Logan Kilpatrick
            </footer>
          </blockquote>
        </section>

        <section class="theatre-modal__section">
          <h3 class="theatre-modal__title">Questions and Answers</h3>
          <dl class="theatre-modal__faq">
            <dt class="theatre-modal__question">
              Did you create this website?
            </dt>
            <dd class="theatre-modal__answer">
              Yes. I originally designed it in Framer, then rebuilt it using
              Jamstack.
            </dd>

            <dt class="theatre-modal__question">What tools did you use?</dt>
            <dd class="theatre-modal__answer">
              Ghost as a headless CMS and Astro to render the site with a lot of
              custom enhancements. I also used Framer for the initial design and
              prototyping, Figma for some of the graphics, and Aseprite for
              pixelart.
            </dd>

            <dt class="theatre-modal__question">
              What are these weird colors and fonts?
            </dt>
            <dd class="theatre-modal__answer">
              A nod to late-'80s CGA graphics.
            </dd>
            <dt class="theatre-modal__question">
              What video game system do you recommend buying?
            </dt>
            <dd class="theatre-modal__answer">
              That would be the Nintendo Switch 2, thank you for asking.
            </dd>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <footer class="theatre-modal__footer">
          <p class="theatre-modal__signoff">
            You read it all the way through, yay!
          </p>
          <img
            class="theatre-modal__signoff-gif"
            src={`${base}/img/yoshi.gif`}
            alt="Yoshi"
          />
        </footer>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
